    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello @RodrigoTomeES!\r\n\r\nServer side rendering on Next.js using [`createInstantSearchRouterNext()`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/instantsearch-next-router/react-hooks/#widget-param-routeroptions) is not supported with [`getStaticProps()`](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/data-fetching/get-static-props).\r\nIn static mode, you can't retrieve the query parameters because pages are generated at build time, thus the `serverUrl` is not correct.\r\n\r\nYou can use `getServerSideProps()` instead as shown here: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/examples/react-hooks/next/pages/index.tsx#L85-L99\r\n\r\nHope that's clear!",
    "created_at": "2023-05-03T16:11:46Z",
